  <!-- EN: <color=#00FFFF><b>They were once ordinary humans, living normal lives until their homeland suffered a sudden invasion. With their home on the brink of destruction, survivors carrying the ember of hope boarded spacecrafts and embarked on a desperate escape. Bloodthirsty pursuers shadowed them relentlessly, mercilessly devouring every step of their retreat. Facing utter desperation, they decided to attempt a perilous traverse through a wormhole, a final gamble for the survival of their civilization. Thus, they journeyed through the space-time rift, crossing unknown cosmic expanses, finally arriving at the distant and unfamiliar Aquila System.\n\nThroughout the vast Aquila, countless habitable planets orbit gentle stars, like undiscovered jewels in the cosmos. Yet the region's high-concentration ether proved a double-edged sword for the new arrivals: both a miraculous substance of potential and a life-threatening toxin. For humans unaccustomed to this environment, the dense ether acted as a slow poison, with prolonged exposure causing irreversible bodily damage.\nMoreover, these planets hosted powerful ether creatures and savage beasts, possessing either strange abilities or ferocious natures, creating formidable challenges for humans attempting to establish new settlements.\nThese spacecrafts, severely damaged from the violent wormhole traverse, could no longer undertake interstellar travel. The passengers had no choice but to remain in Aquila, making it their only home.\nConfronting this hostile new world, the survivors refused to retreat. They initiated various adaptation programmes, from genetic modifications to mechanical prosthetics, trying every possible method for human survival. As time went by, through countless trials, failures, hardships and perseverance, they finally succeeded.\nThey were no longer the humans they once were, but had become a new existence: "Drivers". With bodies resonating with ether and minds integrated with machanism, they began a new chapter under the heaven of Aquila, guarding this sector while exploring unknown possibilities.\n\nProliferating in their unique way, Drivers show obvious differences when being compared to pure mechanoids. Drivers integrate not with lifeless metal machanism, but with a highly evolved "biomechanism" tissue. This tissue differs from any known synthetic material or traditional biological structure, perfectly combining mechanical resilience with biological adaptability.\nApproximately 40% of a Driver's body consists of this unique biomechanism tissue, integrated not only into organs, bones and skin, but deeply interconnected with their own cells and tissues, achieving profound symbiosis. This process begins during gestation stage in the mother's womb, with embryos undergoing a series of "modifications" before birth, ensuring every newborn Driver inherits these distinctive powers and capabilities.</b></color> -->
